Media Release: Update on the coronavirus by Premier Alan Winde 16 December 2020 As of 1pm on 16 December, the Western Cape has 26 817 active Covid-19 infections with a total of 160 800 confirmed Covid-19 cases and 128 750 recoveries.eval(ez_write_tag([[300,250],'politicsweb_co_za-box-3','ezslot_0',112,'0','0'])); Total confirmed COVID-19 cases 160 800 Total recoveries 128 750 Total deaths 5233 Total active cases (currently infected patients) 26 817 Tests conducted 917 235 Hospitalisations 2045 with 280 of these in ICU or high care The Western Cape Covid-19 data dashboard also features additional data including active cases per sub-district, active cases per 100 000 and 7-day moving averages. Access the data dashboard here: https://coronavirus.westerncape.gov.za/covid-19-dashboard The Western Cape has recorded 57 additional deaths, bringing the total number of COVID-19 related deaths in the province to 5176. We send our condolences to their loved ones at this time. Issued by Office of the Western Cape Premier, 16 December 2020 eval(ez_write_tag([[468,60],'politicsweb_co_za-medrectangle-3','ezslot_9',113,'0','0'])); 